<subsection xml:id="subsec-learning-objectives">
    <title>Course Learning Objectives</title>

    <p>
        Upon successful completion of this course:
    </p>
    <p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <p>
                  Students will demonstrate the appropriate graphical and numerical descriptive statistics to summarize different types of data.

                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                   Students will apply basic probability and probability distribution concepts to business scenarios.

                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                 Students will utilize tools of inferential statistics to estimate population parameters and test claims made about population parameters within business contexts.

                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                  Students will build and assess regression models to analyze relationships between variables.

                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                   Students will perform data analysis by selecting the appropriate quantitative tool (Microsoft Excel).

                </p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>




    
</subsection>



